I came home - for about - I can't remember now - but they'd a big family had that doctor you know and there was a lot of work to do. And his daughter was the - dispenser. I really went - to help her, to go to the surgery and get the bottles out and 
bring to her, you see, and say who it was wanted medicine. That was really my first job. And I did that for about a year.
